---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms"
  description="Plain-language terms for using this site and engaging Valkyrie Remedy."
>
  <main class="vr-shell vr-stub">
    <div class="vr-stub__row" data-reveal>
      <span class="vr-eyebrow">— Terms ⁄ §00</span>
      <div class="vr-prose">
        <h1 class="vr-h2">Terms.</h1>
        <p class="vr-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="vr-body">
          These are the terms that govern your use of this site and the
          services described on it. They are deliberately short and
          plain. The actual engagement is governed by the written scope
          you sign before work begins; that document controls if there's
          any conflict with this page.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">The site.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          The pages here describe services I offer. They are not an offer
          you can accept by clicking a button — every engagement begins
          with a written scope, signed by both of us, before work starts.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Booking deposits.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          The $50 deposit for an intro call is collected by Stripe via
          Cal.com. It's credited in full toward any engagement we agree
          to. If we don't move forward, the deposit pays for the time you
          had on the call. Refunds for cancellations made more than 48
          hours before the call are honored on request.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Engagements.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          Every engagement is governed by its written scope: deliverables,
          timeline, price, what's in, what's out, and warranty terms (if
          any). Rebuilds include a 30-day warranty on what I built;
          everything else is scoped per engagement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Confidentiality.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          Anything you share in the course of an engagement — code,
          documentation, internal processes, business context — is
          confidential. I sign NDAs on request and default to treating
          everything as confidential whether one is in place or not.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Limits.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          I do my best work and stand behind it, but I can't guarantee
          outcomes that depend on factors outside what I touched. To the
          extent allowed by law, my liability for any engagement is
          limited to the fees paid for that engagement. Nothing in these
          terms attempts to exclude liability that can't lawfully be
          excluded.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Governing law.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in
          which I operate, and disputes will be resolved there. The
          specific jurisdiction is identified on each engagement's signed
          scope.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Changes.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          If these terms change, the date at the top updates. If you
          have a live engagement, the terms in effect when you signed
          your scope continue to apply to that work.
        </p>

        <h2 class="vr-prose__h">Plain talk.</h2>
        <p class="vr-body">
          This page is a working draft authored by an engineer, not a
          lawyer. It exists to set honest expectations. For binding
          language consult a professional. If you have questions or
          concerns, email
          <a href="mailto:hello@valkyrieremedy.com">hello@valkyrieremedy.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .vr-stub {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-block: 4rem 6rem;
  }
  .vr-stub__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(120px, 200px) 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
    padding-block: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .vr-stub__row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  }
  .vr-prose {
    max-width: 78ch;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .vr-prose .vr-body { max-width: none; margin: 0; }
  .vr-prose__h {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--vr-serif);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--vr-step-2);
    color: var(--vr-bone);
  }
  .vr-prose a {
    color: var(--vr-gold);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .vr-prose a:hover { color: var(--vr-iron-warm); }
</style>
